$interpreted: Joan: Let me tell you a love story. This one takes place in a snowy kingdom, far away...
Naive Princess: What gives!? I didn't write 'jewels' on my Christmas list! I just wanted cute guys!!
Naive Princess: Where are the cute guys, mom and dad!?
Heroic Knight: ...Ah, Princess...
Naive Princess: Don't try and convince me! I'm not going back home!
Heroic Knight: No, I just wanted to say that your outfit is a bit... inappropriate. If His Majesty saw, I might lose this month's salary... again.
Naive Princess: Hmph, what do you know!?
Naive Princess: Haven't you ever read a love story? Rule #1: The princess dresses up like a commoner, then runs into her true love!
Naive Princess: Remember to feign a dizzy spell for maximum impact.
Mystery Man: ...You...
Naive Princess: (He's so close to me... is he gonna try and kiss me!?)
Naive Princess: Ah, that was too close, too fast~!
Heroic Knight: Apologies, she's not feeling quite well today. Did you need something?
Mystery Man: Forgive me, but... I feel like this is love at first sight...
Mystery Man: Something's come over me... I've never felt this way before.
Naive Princess: (What a cornball... Wait a second, is he confessing!? Oh my, am I gonna get a boyfriend!?)
Naive Princess: Ah...
Heroic Knight: Princess, watch out!
Mystery Man: Alas, the bell... I'm afraid we must part ways.
Mystery Man: I know you can do it. Remove the mask and uncover the truth! Follow me! Let's search for the Star of True Love, together!
Naive Princess: ...Um, kind of a weird proposal, but...
Naive Princess: Okay! I do!
Naive Princess: Wait, what about my ring!? You're supposed to put a ring on my finger first!

Heroic Knight: You've read too many stories, princess—
Princess! There's something fishy about this guy!
Heroic Knight: Men like him... you're just going to fall further into his trap.
Heroic Knight: ....
Naive Princess: ...Huh? I definitely saw him run this way...
Naive Princess: is this... a masquerade ball?
Naive Princess: Everyone's wearing a mask... how am I supposed to find him?
Heroic Knight: Eh, maybe we should just—
Naive Princess: Wow, this is just like out of a storybook!
Naive Princess: The princess has to make her way through a bunch of obstacles to find true love and live happily ever after!
Heroic Knight: Princess, I think you're missing the point!
Naive Princess: Oh, right! The point is... if you want a good Christmas gift, you've got to take it for yourself!
Naive Princess: I'm gonna rip off all these masks, and get the guy! Come on, Mr. Knight!
Joan: Hoho! Just what has the princess gotten herself into? Will she be able to find her true love!?
Heroic Knight: ...A merry Christmas, indeed...
